Be you⌃ not as horse and mule, which have no understanding;
31:9 See Alex. ἄγξεις
but you must constrain their jaws with bit and curb, lest they should come near to you.

Their venom is like
that of a serpent; as
that of a deaf asp, and that stops her ears;

Come and behold the works of God;
he is terrible in
his counsels beyond the children of men.

And he shall live, and there shall be given him of the gold of Arabia: and
men shall pray for him continually;
and all the day shall they praise him.

The trees of the plain shall be full
of sap;
even the cedars of Libanus which he has planted.

